This module has been about getting you ready to start to learn the building blocks of any C++ application.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:14,000
So to start with, I would encourage you to go and get Visual C++ Express.

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:19,000
If you have another version of Visual Studio, that's great, but Visual C++ Express is free and it will work

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:25,000
fine for all of the demos that we are doing. And its relatively a straight forward application to use and to

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:31,000
get comfortable and familiar with. Because it's an integrated development environment, you can edit your code.

6
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:35,000
You can see those red wigglies when you make a mistake while you are editing your code.

7
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,000
You can build as a combination of compiling and linking.

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
It's not really terribly important at the moment to understand them.

9
