And you see how to run an application without debugging or with debugging, and the possible problem

12
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,000
when you are running a console application, that if you run without debugging,

13
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
it just kind of runs out the end and you don't see the output.

14
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:08,000
And how running without debugging causes, Visual Studio will pause it for you, give you a chance to read the output.

15
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:14,000
That's generally what we are going to want to do. Because console applications are the simplest,

16
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:19,000
that's what all the demos in this course are going to be, and that's what you are going to be using to get

17
